overview: Tempo is predicted to be very genuine. Scratchings significantly affected this race. ARGYLE BELLE can struggle to convert good run into wins, but she comes off a good platform in her last two runs. Down in class off last start alongside a wider draw and good rider change all help. HAYLIN ROUGE did well to bounce back off a flat run and achieve a new personal best rating and win her maiden in excellent style. Query is whether that level can be sustained here, but she is still a threat. AYERS ROCK has been going well, but hasn't won in a while. CHAMPAGNE LUCY next best.
